---
/**
 * DemoCard.astro
 * Pure UI component for the WikiSure™ demo.
 * NO logic, NO API calls, NO state outside the DOM.
 * Perspective: Platform Provider (Embedded Insurance)
 */
---

<style>
  .card {
    max-width: 980px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    background: white;
    border-radius: 18px;
    padding: 36px;
    box-shadow: 0 20px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
    font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", sans-serif;
  }

  h1 { margin: 0 0 6px 0; font-size: 28px; }
  h2 { margin-top: 32px; font-size: 20px; }

  .subtle {
    color: #6b7280;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  label {
    display: block;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }

  input, textarea {
    width: 100%;
    padding: 10px;
    border-radius: 10px;
    border: 1px solid #d1d5db;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    font-size: 14px;
  }

  textarea { min-height: 120px; }

  .grid2 {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 16px;
    margin-top: 10px;
  }

  button {
    margin-top: 16px;
    padding: 12px 16px;
    border-radius: 12px;
    border: none;
    background: #2563eb;
    color: white;
    font-weight: 700;
    cursor: pointer;
  }

  .hint {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: #6b7280;
    margin-top: 8px;
  }

  .explain {
    margin-top: 12px;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: #374151;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  #decision {
    margin-top: 16px;
    padding: 16px;
    border-radius: 12px;
    background: #f9fafb;
    border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
  }
</style>

<div class="card">
  <h1>WikiSure™ Demo</h1>
  <p class="subtle">
    <strong>Perspective:</strong> Platform Provider offering embedded insurance.<br />
    This demo illustrates how shared semantic governance supports human-in-the-loop
    decision-making across insurers, partners and regulators.
  </p>

  <!-- STEP 1 -->
  <h2>1. Define a Term</h2>
  <label>Term</label>
  <input id="term" placeholder="e.g. Embedded Insurance Consent" />

  <div class="hint">
    As a platform, you must align terminology across insurers, APIs, UX flows and compliance teams.
  </div>

  <!-- STEP 2 -->
  <h2>2. Compare Definitions</h2>
  <div class="grid2">
    <div>
      <label>Canonical Definition (Baseline)</label>
      <textarea id="canonical" placeholder="Approved baseline definition"></textarea>
    </div>
    <div>
      <label>Proposed Change (Draft)</label>
      <textarea id="draft" placeholder="New or adapted definition"></textarea>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="hint">
    Changes often arise from new partners, new markets or regulatory clarification.
  </div>

  <!-- STEP 3 -->
  <h2>3. AI as Assistant (Illustrative)</h2>
  <button type="button">AI Suggest</button>
  <div class="hint">
    AI helps highlight ambiguities or missing context — it does not decide.
  </div>

  <!-- STEP 4 -->
  <h2>4. Governance Decision</h2>
  <button type="button">Run Governance Check</button>

  <div id="decision">
    <strong>Governance Outcome (Illustrative):</strong>
    <div class="explain">
      From a platform perspective, the proposed definition is acceptable
      <em>with conditions</em>.<br />
      Documentation must be aligned, partners must share the same interpretation,
      and regulatory expectations must be respected.
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- FINAL AHA -->
  <h2>Why this matters for platforms</h2>
  <div class="explain">
    WikiSure™ does not replace insurers, platforms or regulators.<br /><br />
    It provides a <strong>shared semantic governance layer</strong> so that:
    <ul>
      <li>Definitions stay consistent across partners</li>
      <li>AI remains explainable and reviewable</li>
      <li>Humans stay accountable for decisions</li>
      <li>Embedded insurance scales without semantic chaos</li>
    </ul>
    <strong>The result:</strong> Faster rollout of embedded insurance —
    without losing regulatory control or human oversight.
  </div>
</div>
